  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The transversus abdominis plane (TAP) block is a regional anesthetic technique for post
      operative pain control after abdominal surgical procedures. Its effectiveness in children
      undergoing laparoscopic appendectomy has not been demonstrated. The investigators evaluate
      its analgesic efficacy over the first 24 post operative hours.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
